      "comment": "NEEDBEE (9) had to work when tackling a higher-graded race last start so prepared to forgive that result. Had won two in a row prior, one of them at this circuit and distance. Draws for a trail and could return to the winners' list. KEAYANG GALLIANO (8) is a newcomer to the Seaton Grima yard from Tasmania where she has put together a string of wins and placings. Cops a wide barrier but with even luck could measure right up. MISTER SEASIDE (7) came from one spot wider and worked but stuck on to place here last week. Go well again. LEXYS ON SONG (10) has struggled a little at his last few but did manage back-to-back wins last month, one of them at Menangle so can do better.",
